Life

 Bamboo bounty

 SANGITA SULTANIA G. ROY

 Enjoy good health, wealth and a steady marriage, all because of an innocuous little plant. So says Feng Shui of tiny bamboo trees that unsuspecting souls mistake as purely decorative pieces. 

 The cluster of bamboo shoots, usually bunched together in a glass bowl with colourful pebbles at the base as sold in gift shops, do look very ornamental indeed. 

 aced on table tops, mantelpieces or any forlorn nook and cranny in the house, these lend a dash of nature and perk up the mood of the room. 

 But Feng Shui professes to put them to better use by placing the apparatus in key directions with significant implications. If you place three stems in the east you are supposed to enjoy good health, while four stems in the south-east is all you need to get wealthy! 

