?The east and the south-east directions are ruled by wood energy,? says Feng Shui expert and Goodlife columnist Pinky Kapoor. But what is health and wealth without love? Not to fret, if your marriage has been on the rocks, just steady the boat by tying two stems with a red ribbon and placing it in the south-west direction, which is believed to be the marriage corner. 

 Add to the lucky charm and the beauty of the whole thing by placing it in a crystal bowl and dropping blue and green marbles in it. ?This helps attract the energy of the elements as well,? advises Pinky. And the best part is, the plant requires little care for all its lofty services. Keep it indoors and just change the water once a week to preserve all its bounty. 

